PvP: Fluted + accurized + Killing Wind/Quickdraw/Firmly Planted + Headseeker/Kill Clip/Moving Target
Pulses do appear to be range capped, so like Cold Denial, its best to focus on stability if you get Killing Wind since KW adds +20 range, + 50 mobility, and +~40  handling. This pulse has standard zoom and iron sights like those on Redrix.

PvP: Hammer/Fluted/Arrowhead Brake + Accurized + Firmly Planted/Moving Target/Killing Wind/No Distractions + Snapshot/Quickdraw/Opening Shot/KC/MKC
This sniper has some interesting rolls. With KC and MKC it can get ohk body shots, and Vorpal makes it one of the ways to counter a behemoth super. However, these all roll in the same slot as the handling perks, so you are giving up better ads and feel for these build perks

PvP: X + Rico/HiCal + Slideshot/Rangefinder + Opening Shot/Vorpal/KC
Of the 140 HCs, Waking has lower base range at 38 therefore it cannot really be a max range weapon, however, it does have great base handing.
Due to the inability to fight at the extended ranges of 140s, sight choice can come down to which is preferred visually. Despite this, the sights which are normally ignored because of the stat penalties they incur (Sureshot & Crossfire) can be worth it to push the range out as far as possible.
Dungeon Perks: Surplus, Vorpal, Thresh

PvE: Any + Lightmag/Flared/Hi-Cal  + Surplus/Rapid Hit + Dfly/Dbreak/Vorpal/Kill Clip
60 base reload + 10 from mag perk + 10/20/40 form vorpal would be sufficient for reloads. Outlaw would max out reload (+60) but its not as consistently procd in higher level content.
Dungeon Perks: Surplus, Vorpal, Thresh.
Hi-Cal can stunlock and knockback PvE enemies.

PvP: Hard/Quick Launch/(Volatile/Confined Launch for minimal velocity) + High Velocity/(Any but High Velocity for minimal velocity) + Tracking + Chain/Vorpal/Unrelenting

PvP: Red Dot 2/Red Dot Micro + Projection Fuse/Particle Repeater + Firmly Planted/Under Pressure + HIR/Rangefinder
This is a PvP Fusion through and through, and with the changes to fusions in S15 its potentially one of the best. As its currently only available from Xur, a god roll of this will be like Gold Dust until it sells one for us all. Keep an eye out for a Firmly Planted/Rangefinder roll with either of the zoom increasing scopes, but Under Pressure is still an excellent perk, with HIR not changing the bolts to kill (confirm?) but offering better damage per bolt, easier cleanup and excellent synergy with Under Pressure
